<HEADLINE>
<P>
NO STEREOTYPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I am a social liberal and a fiscal conservative. I give money to the Nature 
Conservancy and the NRA. I admire Martin Luther King Jr. and George Patton. 
</P>
<P>
 I am peaceful but I am not a pacifist. I'm pro-choice but I don't support 
animal research. I think the grunt in the foxhole and the anti-war protester 
both served their country well. 
</P>
<P>
 I think there's too much violence on TV but I loved "Die Hard." I think we 
were wrong in Vietnam but I fly my POW-MIA flag. I think a person has a right 
to burn his flag if he wants to and I cry when they play the national anthem. 
My faith is in God but I don't go to church. 
</P>
<P>
 I am not a liberal, a conservative, a hippie or a fat cat. I am not a bigot, a 
bleeding heart or a member of the media or the elite. I cannot be categorized. 
I cannot be stereotyped. I will not fit in a pigeonhole. I am full of 
inconsistencies but I am not inconsistent. 
</P>
<P>
 All people on welfare are not lazy. All people who own guns are not nuts. All 
people in gangs are not killers. All cops are not pigs. All Republicans are not 
heartless. And all Democrats are not Commies. 
</P>
<P>
 We are each unique; individuals whose values are molded through every moment 
of our lives. We are all Americans. We are America. 
</P>
<P>
 WILLIAM G. SHANK 
</P>
<P>
 Redondo Beach 
</P>
