<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; OPPORTUNITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE CART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The U.S. Soccer Federation is not about to waste this opportunity to learn 
from the World Cup experience, after other chances have slipped through. 
</P>
<P>
 For the first time, the USSF has dispatched two persons to each of the nine 
World Cup venues to scout the games and file reports.At the end of each of the 
rounds, the reports will be tabulated and entered into a computer. 
</P>
<P>
 Included in the reports is tactical information on each of the 24 World Cup 
teams and an analysis of tendencies of key players. 
</P>
<P>
 The U.S. team is provided the information on a daily basis and a complete 
report will published after the World Cup and disseminated to soccer coaches in 
the United States. JULIE CART 
</P>
</TEXT>
