<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROB HUGHES, The Times of London 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "Germany, on the evidence of two solid, grinding and efficient performances, 
has become the first team to virtually qualify for the second phase. The 
Germans still parade their gamesmanship, with Juergen Klinsmann still combining 
dashing athleticism with almost farcical ability to con the referees. Later on, 
though, I believe that it will be seen that this is a German version nearly 
four years older than 1990, one that looked vulnerable in defense when Spain 
attacked on both flanks, and one that will run out of lung power when the South 
Americans, or possibly even the Nigerians, prevail." 
