<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; INSTANT HUMBLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Some international journalists had to bite their tongues when Bulgarian star 
forward Hristo Stoichkov stood on the interview podium Sunday and presented 
himself as a team player. 
</P>
<P>
 "I do not see myself as a star," he said after his team's 4-0 victory over 
Greece. "I am just one of 22 (players). Although I play for Barcelona, I hope I 
do not have the star attitude." 
</P>
<P>
 Bulgarian bull? 
</P>
<P>
 Stoichkov has the reputation of a self-centered hothead. Said Barcelona Coach 
Johan Cruyff of Stoichkov: "Teammates are just people to be used for his own 
individual ends and then thrown away." CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
