<P>
 Striker Luis Garcia, who scored both goals for Mexico in a 2-1 victory over 
Ireland on Friday, has flu and missed Sunday's practice but will be able to 
play Tuesday against Italy at Washington, team doctor Alfonso Diaz said. 
</P>
<P>
 A one-game ban for Cameroon defender Rigobert Bahanag Song, sent off for a 
foul in a game against Brazil on Friday, has been increased to two games after 
FIFA, soccer's world governing body, said it had made a mistake. 
</P>
<P>
 Spanish defender Rafael Alkorta will miss today's Group C match against 
Bolivia in Chicago because of a calf injury, Coach Javier Clemente said. 
