<P>
HORSE RACING; LURE SURGES LATE TO WIN THE CAESARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lure overtook Fourstars Allstar in deep stretch and won the $500,000 Caesars 
International Handicap by a nose at Atlantic City Race Course on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Lure, ridden by Mike Smith, completed the 1 3/16 miles on turf in 1:52 3/5 and 
paid $3.20, $2.20 and $2.10.Fourstars Allstar returned $3 and $2.10 and Star Of 
Cozzene paid $2.10. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Virginia Rapids rallied to win the $100,000-added Tom Fool Stakes by a head 
over Cherokee Run at Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Boundary, previously undefeated in five starts, finished another 1 3/4 lengths 
back in third in the field of five. 
</P>
<P>
 Ridden by Jean-Luc Samyn, Virginia Rapids covered seven furlongs in 1:22 1/5 
and paid $11.60, $4.40 and $2.40. Cherokee Run paid $3.20 and $2.20 and 
Boundary returned $2.40. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Balanchine pulled away in the stretch and won the Irish Derby by 4 1/2 lengths 
at the Curragh near Dublin. She became the first to sweep the Derby and Epsom 
Oaks since Salsabil in 1990. 
</P>
<P>
 Owner Sheikh Mohammed plans to rest the filly before considering a challenge 
for the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe in France. 
</P>
</TEXT>
