<TEXT>
<P>
 Orders for Machine Tools Fall: Orders for American-made machine tools dropped 
18.5% in May after reaching their highest level of the year the month before. 
The Assn. for Manufacturing Technology said machine tool orders totaled $336.85 
million in May, down from $413.50 million in April. But orders were up 6.7% 
compared with May, 1993, and year-to-date orders were 20.8% ahead of the same 
period in 1993. 
</P>
