<TEXT>
<P>
 Department Store Sales Slip: Sales nationwide fell in May to $6.76 billion, a 
4.3% decline from the year-earlier period, the Japan Department Store Assn. 
said.That marks the 27th straight monthly decline. Clothing sales fell 4.1% and 
food sales dropped 2.1%. Furniture and consumer electronics sales fell 10.2%. 
Separately, the Japan Chain Stores Assn. said sales at chain stores in May 
declined 2.3% in May from a year earlier to $12.6 billion. 
</P>
