</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sales Rise, but Growth Is Slowing: Manufacturing sales rose 10% in the year 
ended March 31 amid signs of a slowdown in the nation's growth, the government 
said.Growth during the January-March quarter slowed to 6% compared to the same 
quarter a year ago, said Dennis Trewin, a government statistician. That was 
down from the 9% growth in the October-December quarter over the year-earlier 
period. Despite the slowing rate of growth, confidence in manufacturing was 
demonstrated by a 40% rise in investment in the January-March quarter compared 
to the year-ago period. 
</P>
