</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bank Revises Growth Prediction Upward: The economy, propelled by brisk exports 
and capital investment, should grow 7.8% this year, the highest rate in three 
years, the Bank of Korea said.The central bank had previously predicted that 
the economy would grow 6.3% this year. Other economic institutions are also 
revising their forecasts upward. The Korean Development Institute, a government 
think tank, recently changed its prediction from 7% to 7.6% growth. The Korean 
economy grew at an 8.8% rate in the first quarter of this year, the highest 
quarterly expansion in more than three years, the bank said. 
</P>
