<HEADLINE>
<P>
HUNTINGTON BEACH'S GONZALEZ PACES COUNTY ALL-STARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tony Gonzalez made a layup with one second left to give a team of Orange 
County basketball all-stars a 116-114 victory over a team from San Diego County 
on Sunday at Del Mar Torrey Pines High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Gonzalez, from Huntington Beach, finished with 37 points and 17 rebounds and 
was selected the game's most valuable player.  
</P>
<P>
 He was selected as the MVP of the Orange County all-star game as well as the 
top player in a game against a Santa Barbara team earlier this month. 
</P>
<P>
 Gonzalez's winning basket came off an assist from Micah Kroeger of Edison. 
</P>
<P>
 Kroeger had 22 points and Gil Gonzales of Orange added 13 points. 
</P>
