<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; RWANDA; REBEL ATTACKS DELAY EVACUATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Huge explosions erupted on Mt. Kigali, the last hilltop in government hands 
overlooking the Rwandan capital, after hours of rebel bombardments brought 
humanitarian operations to a standstill.Dozens of casualties poured into the 
Red Cross hospital on the government side as rebel mortar bombs exploded all 
around. The Red Cross aborted plans to evacuate about 60 wounded from its 
overflowing hospital across the battle lines to the King Faisal hospital. The 
U.N. Assistance Mission again put off the evacuation of 200 people -- mostly 
unaccompanied Tutsi children -- from the St. Michel church in government 
territory. 
</P>
