<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; JUST WIN TIE, BABY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Belgian Coach Paul Van Himst, whose team has qualified for the second round, 
will give a few of his regulars the day off Wednesday when Belgium plays Saudi 
Arabia at Washington, D.C. 
</P>
<P>
 But he's not tanking the game. Only one or two starters will rest, because Van 
Himst still wants a tie or victory to clinch the Group F championship.That 
would ensure Belgium returns to Orlando on July 4 for its first round-of-16 
game, against the second-place team in Group E. 
</P>
<P>
 "The team is improving, and by (Saturday's) win over Holland we are in a 
comfortable position, but we need a point to be first in our group," he said 
Sunday. "The players wish to stay here and not to travel. We are doing fine 
here, and I told them if they want to stay here, they must take a point at 
least." HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</TEXT>
