<TEXT>
<P>
 The Federal Trade Commission is investigating the PGA Tour for possible 
"unfair methods of competition," according to Brandweek Magazine. It said the 
FTC is interviewing organizers of "unofficial" pro golf events, many of them 
made-for-TV productions whose organizers must pay a rights fee -- generally 
$200,000 to $400,000 -- to the PGA Tour in order to secure tour players. 
</P>
