<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: WESTLAKE; GUNMAN ROBS EATERY, THREATENS EMPLOYEES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County sheriff's deputies were searching Sunday for a suspect who 
threatened to kill two employees before cleaning out a safe at a Westlake 
Domino's Pizza restaurant, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Albert Ramos, the restaurant's assistant manager, said he saw the man talking 
on a pay phone outside the eatery in the 2800 block of Agoura Road moments 
before the restaurant's driver returned from a delivery around midnight 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 "When my driver punched in the code to come inside, once he opened the door, 
this guy pulled out a gun and put it to his head," Ramos said. "He told us to 
get all the money, threatened to kill us and told us to (lie down on) the 
floor." 
</P>
<P>
 The suspect fled with about $349 of the restaurant's money, and took the 
wallets of Ramos, 24, and driver Scott William, 21, police and Ramos said. The 
suspect, a white male in his early 20s, was wearing a black T-shirt and dark 
pants, had short brown hair and a goatee. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
