<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: CAMARILLO; CONTROLLED BRUSH FIRE DRILL PLANNED TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gearing up for a busy fire season, firefighters will race to a preset brush 
fire in Camarillo today to test their skills while reducing brush in the area. 
</P>
<P>
 The controlled burn, planned for 9 a.m., will be set across 12 acres of light 
brush just outside the north entrance of Camarillo State Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Fire officials said they are confident they have created safe conditions for 
the drill. A path has been cleared around the field and crews from the Ventura 
County, Oxnard, Ventura, California Department of Forestry and Los Angeles 
County fire departments will be on hand. 
</P>
<P>
 The burn will be postponed if high winds create too great a hazard, officials 
said. MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
