ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: CENTRAL; GARDEN GROVE; MAN SHOT DURING SCUFFLE IN PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 23-year-old suspected gang member was in critical condition Sunday after 
being shot four times by a member of his own gang, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Juan De La Torre of Garden Grove, who was wounded in the wrist, leg and 
abdomen, was taken to UCI Medical Center in Orange after the 5 p.m. shooting at 
Woodbury Park. 
</P>
<P>
 De La Torre and another man were in the park when they began to argue, Sgt. 
Mark Byrne said. The disagreement escalated into a fistfight and then one of 
the men brandished a gun. 
</P>
<P>
 "There was a struggle for the gun," Byrne said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police detained a suspect but released him after De La Torre refused to 
identify the man as his attacker or cooperate in the investigation. 
</P>
<P>
 Byrne said investigators believe both men are members of the same Garden Grove 
gang. 
</P>
