<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: CENTRAL; GARDEN GROVE; SHOOTING VICTIM, 19, IS IN FAIR 
CONDITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 19-year-old Santa Ana man who was shot while traveling on the Garden Grove 
Freeway was in fair condition Sunday, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Giang Nguyen was a passenger in a car about midnight Saturday when a least one 
occupant of a brown Toyota Camry fired at the vehicle he was riding in, Garden 
Grove Police Sgt. Mark Byrne said. 
</P>
<P>
 Nguyen was struck in the arm, lung and stomach, police said. The shooting 
occurred on the westbound freeway between Brookhurst Street and Magnolia Avenue 
while he was riding in a car with a friend, Phil Dang of Westminster. 
</P>
<P>
 The shooting is under investigation. No suspects or motive have been 
identified. 
</P>
<P>
 Byrne said Dang and Nguyen had been at a party earlier in the evening and were 
on their way home when they noticed that they were being followed by another 
car. The Camry pulled along side and opened fire. 
</P>
<P>
 After the shooting, Dang drove Nguyen to the Garden Grove police station, 
where Dang knocked on a window to get the attention of officers. 
</P>
<P>
 Paramedics transferred Nguyen to UCI Medical Center in Orange. 
</P>
</TEXT>
