<TEXT>
<P>
 The water district's Board of Directors is expected to approve an 
$82.5-million capital projects budget tonight that calls for the construction 
of a new reservoir and pipelines. 
</P>
<P>
 Ron Young, general manager of the Irvine Ranch Water District, said the 
various projects contained in the budget will be paid for by water connection 
fees and property tax assessments. 
</P>
